Package it.polimi.deib.se2019.sanp4.adrenaline.common.exceptions

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    BoardNotFoundException
    Thrown when a requested board (e.g. by id) is not available for retrieval
    CardNotFoundException
    Thrown when a requested card cannot be created/returned, either because it has not been loaded or because it does not belong to a specific collection.
    DuplicateIdException
    Thrown when trying to insert a new value in a map, which should have a unique key, but the key is already associated to another value.
    FullCapacityException
    Indicates that an item you're trying to add to a collection (e.g. a Weapon to a Player) cannot be added because that collection is not allowed by game rules to have more than a certain amount of items (capacity).
    LoginException
    Thrown when a login request fails
    NotEnoughAmmoException
    Thrown when a player has not enough ammo cubes to pay a cost.
    PlayerNotFoundException
    An exception used when an operation targeting a player fails because the player cannot be affected by it (e.g. removing a player from a square)
    UnknownIdException
    Thrown when performing an operation that involves on object which has to be retrieved from a given identifier, but the object with that identifier could not be obtained.
